subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia. Tergite VIII broader than long, apex truncated and slightly emarginated, densely clothed with short hairs (
Fig. 6d
); tegmen curved in lateral view; parameres elongate, mostly covered with long setae on apical half; each paramere with transverse oblique ridge covered with dense fine hairs on ventral side (
Fig. 6a–c
); median lobe 1.3 times as long as tegmen and slightly curved in lateral view; median struts nearly 3/5 times as long as whole median lobe; dorsal plate slightly longer than ventral plate; apex of ventral plate slightly pointed; median foramen rounded (
Fig. 6e
); endophallus with 2 pairs of rods on apical portion, longer pair very slender and baculiform, about 2 times as long as shorter pair (
Fig. 6f
).

Female genitalia (
Fig. 6g
): Capsule of spermatheca with sclerotized rounded apical lobe and a stalk; spermathecal duct longer than capsule; spermathecal gland extended from strongly sclerotized ring attached to spermathecal duct.
